net.dempsy.config

Class Cluster

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dempsy.config.Cluster

  • public class Cluster
extends Object

    Conceptually, a Cluster is the collection of all Message Processors that handle the same 'message type' across a an entire application and potentially distributed across a network. It represents a logical step in the processing stream of an application.

    For example, in the Word Count example from the User Guide, all of the instances of WordCount that represent the step in the chain of processing after the Adaptor are in the same Cluster.

    See Also:
    ClusterId
